          "captureNotes": "Formal OLG model showing entry-level automation can raise output on adoption yet reduce long-run growth and welfare by reallocating novices away from the most productive experts and slowing best-practice diffusion, even without reducing entry-level employment. Supplies the microfoundation for the broken-bottom-rung pipeline-narrowing mechanism."
